<subSubSection id="C33D9BB5FFD5FF8AFF7AE6CFFDD0FC81" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B98C83EFFD5FF8AFF7AE6CFFDD0FC81" blockId="21.[151,1436,152,818]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B953142CFFD5FF8AFF7AE6CFFEC3FCBA" bold="true" box="[198,312,751,777]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks</emphasis>
. In contrast to 
<taxonomicName id="4C27B3BDFFD5FF8AFE5BE6D0FD72FCBA" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Walsingham" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[487,649,752,777]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Megalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submicans">
<emphasis id="B953142CFFD5FF8AFE5BE6D0FD72FCBA" box="[487,649,752,777]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. submicans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which appears to be fairly widespread in the Caribbean, 
<taxonomicName id="4C27B3BDFFD5FF8AFA95E6D0FF2BFC82" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Megalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jamaicana">
<emphasis id="B953142CFFD5FF8AFA95E6D0FF2BFC82" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. jamaicana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from 
<collectingCountry id="F33088AEFFD5FF8AFE79E738FDDCFC81" box="[453,551,792,818]" name="Jamaica" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
